    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you see three sharps in a piece of music, locate that position on the Circle of Fifths to identify the key. Three sharps correspond to A major (or its relative minor, F# minor), which sits three steps clockwise from C major. Simply find the spot labeled \"3 sharps\" on the circle, and the key name next to it tells you the tonality of the song. This method works regardless of whether the music is written in major or minor, as the circle displays both relationships.",
